message:
@mp131 My personal belief is that story must be more important than theory. But I'm not sure how this works in practice. If I need a nuclear bomb, the bomb is more important than the physics... but I'm not going to get very far if I don't understand the physics.

Either way, I don't think I understand the theory at all. Understanding the theory (to me) would mean understanding how one appreciation (female mental sex) affects another (swap it, spin it, carry it, leave it, etc.) Have Chris and Melanie even released that information?

So, what I do, is focus on the building blocks they provide. What does a Benchmark mean? How is it used? If that's what you mean by studying the theory more, I'm all in.
